				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA Ambidexterity ...?<a name="34429"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 13 04 12:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I didn't get ambidex until after I had 200+ AAs.
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't recommend Ambidex until you have the following AAs:
<br />

<br />
IM3
<br />
SM3
<br />
Bellow
<br />
ND3
<br />
PE
<br />
CA3
<br />
LR5
<br />
JF3
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ambidex, like Harmonius attack a decent AA but even with them, your melee dps is still going to be somewhat lacking. 
<br />
AAs that improve your songs, pulling ability and survivability are far more valuable than those that increase your melee dps.
<br />

<br />
The previous poster mentioned Combat Stability. There isn't a whole lot of value in CS unless you do a lot of melee soloing or you tank a lot. </span></td>
