				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA Ambidexterity ...?<a name="34446"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 13 04 1:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ship, 
<br />

<br />
It doesn't work that way.  Firstly, mainhand and offhand aren't 'linked' in that way.  Secondly, procs have been coded such that they scale with the effective delay of the weapon (taking into account slows and haste).  
<br />

<br />
The ONLY things that affect proc rate are 1) dex, 2) weapon affinity, and 3) combat effects.
<br />

<br />
With 305 dex, you get 2 procs per min (ppm) main and 1 ppm offhand.  
<br />

<br />
Weapon affinity 5 (30 AA's) will give you about +45% PPM main and offhand.
<br />

<br />
Wyndaria.
<br />
</span></td>
