				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA Ambidexterity ...?<a name="34628"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 14 04 11:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Okay, I think I missed something.  It was my understanding that on every swing on your main hand, dual-wield &quot;rolls&quot; and you have a chance for your secondary to swing as well, per &quot;turn&quot;.  The more often primary swings in X amount of time, the more often you get a dual-wield check.  Ambidexterity just increases the chance at a dual-wield check success off of your primary swing.  
<br />

<br />
Now the proc itself is seperate.  You are correct in that is based on dex, combat effects, and wa checks.  If you swing your weapon, whether in primary or secondary slot, regardless of hit or miss and if you are successful on your proc &quot;roll&quot; for that swing, you will proc.  Ambi does NOT affect success on a proc &quot;roll&quot;.  
<br />

<br />
The more you dual-wield, the more you have a chance at the secondary go through a proc check.  This should help keep DotB up as much as possible, especially for those that have epic in secondary, such as myself.  
<br />

<br />
Please clarify if I was wrong in any of this.</span></td>
