				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA Ambidexterity ...?<a name="34636"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 14 04 11:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Short answer: No, ambidexterity does not affect your proc rate. Wyndaria is spot on.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It was my understanding that on every swing on your main hand, dual-wield &quot;rolls&quot; and you have a chance for your secondary to swing as well per &quot;turn&quot;. The more often primary swings in X amount of time, the more often you get a dual-wield check.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
No idea about this, I'm not a melee expert but I didn't think it worked like this.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Now the proc itself is seperate. That is based on dex, atk, wa checks.</span></blockquote>
<br />
The proc is based on Dex and WA, plus some weapons have a proc rate modifier. Nothing else matters (as Metallica like to say :p), so adding atk will not help you.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">If you swing your secondary, regardless of hit or miss, and if you are successful on your proc &quot;roll&quot; for that swing, you will proc. </span></blockquote>
<br />
You don't get a proc &quot;roll&quot; per swing as such. Proc rate is unrelated to your swing rate. As stated above, proc rate is only based on dex and WA. Without WA and with 305 dex, you will always averate 2ppm main-hand, 1ppm off-hand. Haste, slows, weapon delays etc are all irrelevant. Sometimes you'll get streaky spells with no procs, and other times streaks with lots, but over time everybody has the same proc rate for a given dex/WA/Weapon. Refer to the steel warrior forums for parses to back this up if interested<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Basically, what I was wanting to affirm was that with Ambi, you get a higher chance at a dual-wield check and with this higher chance you also get a higher chance at your secondary proc'n (which we know is based on dex, atk, wa).</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Nope, sorry :(</span></td>
