				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA Ambidexterity ...?<a name="34647"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 14 04 12:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Dual wield checks are no longer tied to primary hand in ANY WAY!  And bards, of all people, should know this.  Think about it -- since the game began, people with dual wield could equip a weapon in primary and a non-weapon in secondary.  This was the norm for some classes.  NO ONE at the start, could equip a weapon in secondary and a non-weapon in primary.  Then during the Kunark expansion, they added the first primary-wieldable instruments.  And that was when they had to change the algorithm for dual wield to what it is now -- it checks based on the delay of the weapon in secondary hand and does not relate IN ANY WAY to primary.  It cannot function in any other way or a non-weapon primary hand object would crash the algorithm.
<br />

<br />
Dual wield checks are NOT tied to primary hand weapon delay and haven't been for a couple of years now.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
